{"pageProps":{"eyebrow":"About","page":{"layout":"document","title":"CUPTI Asynchronous Activity Tracing Tutorial","description":"The GitHub repo and complete tutorial is available at <https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/cupti-tutorial.","descriptionIsExcerpt":true,"bodyHtml":"<blockquote>\n<p>The GitHub repo and complete tutorial is available at <a href=\"https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/cupti-tutorial\">https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/cupti-tutorial</a>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2 id=\"introduction\">Introduction</h2>\n<p>Profiling GPU applications can significantly impact performance if not done carefully. This tutorial demonstrates how to use CUPTI's asynchronous activity tracing to collect performance data with minimal impact on your application's execution time. You'll learn how to collect detailed GPU and API activity traces while your application continues to run at full speed.</p>\n<h2 id=\"what-youll-learn\">What You'll Learn</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>How to set up asynchronous buffer handling with CUPTI</li>\n<li>Techniques for non-blocking collection of performance data</li>\n<li>Processing profiling information in a separate thread</li>\n<li>Minimizing the performance impact of profiling</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"asynchronous-vs-synchronous-tracing\">Asynchronous vs. Synchronous Tracing</h2>\n<p>Before diving into the code, let's understand why asynchronous tracing matters:</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<table><thead><tr><th>Synchronous Tracing</th><th>Asynchronous Tracing</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Blocks application during buffer processing</td><td>Application continues running during buffer processing</td></tr><tr><td>Simple implementation</td><td>Requires thread-safe handling</td></tr><tr><td>Higher performance impact</td><td>Lower performance impact</td></tr><tr><td>Suitable for short test runs</td><td>Suitable for production or long-running applications</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<h2 id=\"code-walkthrough\">Code Walkthrough</h2>\n<h3 id=\"1-setting-up-asynchronous-buffer-handling\">1. Setting Up Asynchronous Buffer Handling</h3>\n<p>The key to asynchronous tracing is configuring CUPTI to use a separate thread for buffer management:</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"cpp\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"cpp\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">void</span><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\"> initTrace</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">()</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">{</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\">  // Enable asynchronous buffer handling</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">  CUpti_ActivityAttribute attr </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">=</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> CUPTI_ACTIVITY_ATTR_CALLBACKS;</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">  CUpti_BuffersCallbackRequestFunc bufferRequested </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">=</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> bufferRequestedCallback;</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">  CUpti_BuffersCallbackCompleteFunc bufferCompleted </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">=</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> bufferCompletedCallback;</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">  </span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">  CUPTI_CALL</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(</span><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">cuptiActivityRegisterCallbacks</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(bufferRequested, bufferCompleted));</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">  </span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\">  // Enable the activity kinds you want to track</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">  CUPTI_CALL</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(</span><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">cuptiActivityEnable</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(CUPTI_ACTIVITY_KIND_DEVICE));</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">  CUPTI_CALL</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(</span><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">cuptiActivityEnable</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(CUPTI_ACTIVITY_KIND_CONTEXT));</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">  CUPTI_CALL</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(</span><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">cuptiActivityEnable</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(CUPTI_ACTIVITY_KIND_DRIVER));</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">  CUPTI_CALL</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(</span><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">cuptiActivityEnable</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(CUPTI_ACTIVITY_KIND_RUNTIME));</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">  CUPTI_CALL</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(</span><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">cuptiActivityEnable</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(CUPTI_ACTIVITY_KIND_MEMCPY));</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">  CUPTI_CALL</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(</span><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">cuptiActivityEnable</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(CUPTI_ACTIVITY_KIND_MEMSET));</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">  CUPTI_CALL</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(</span><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">cuptiActivityEnable</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(CUPTI_ACTIVITY_KIND_KERNEL));</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">  CUPTI_CALL</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(</span><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">cuptiActivityEnable</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(CUPTI_ACTIVITY_KIND_CONCURRENT_KERNEL));</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">  </span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\">  // Capture timestamp for normalizing times</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">  CUPTI_CALL</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(</span><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">cuptiGetTimestamp</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">&#x26;</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">startTimestamp));</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">}</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<h3 id=\"2-asynchronous-buffer-request-callback\">2. Asynchronous Buffer Request Callback</h3>\n<p>The buffer request callback is similar to the synchronous version, but now it must be thread-safe:</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"cpp\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"cpp\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">static</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\"> void</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> CUPTIAPI</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">bufferRequestedCallback</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">uint8_t</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\"> **</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">buffer, </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">size_t</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\"> *</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">size, </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">size_t</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\"> *</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">maxNumRecords)</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">{</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">  *</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">size </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">=</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> BUF_SIZE;</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">  </span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\">  // Allocate a buffer with extra space for alignment</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">  *</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">buffer </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">=</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> (</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">uint8_t</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\"> *</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">)</span><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">malloc</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">*</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">size </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">+</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> ALIGN_SIZE);</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">  if</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> (</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">*</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">buffer </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">==</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> NULL</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">) {</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">    printf</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">\"Error: Out of memory</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">\\n</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">\"</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">);</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">    exit</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">-</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">1</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">);</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">  }</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">  </span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\">  // Align the buffer to ALIGN_SIZE</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">  *</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">buffer </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">=</span><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\"> ALIGN_BUFFER</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">*</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">buffer, ALIGN_SIZE);</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">  </span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\">  // No limit on the number of records</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">  *</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">maxNumRecords </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">=</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> 0</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">;</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">}</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<h3 id=\"3-asynchronous-buffer-completion-callback\">3. Asynchronous Buffer Completion Callback</h3>\n<p>The most important part is the buffer completion callback, which now runs in a separate thread:</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"cpp\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"cpp\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">static</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\"> void</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> CUPTIAPI</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">bufferCompletedCallback</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(CUcontext ctx, </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">uint32_t</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> streamId, </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">uint8_t</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\"> *</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">buffer, </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">size_t</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> size, </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">size_t</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> validSize)</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">{</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">  CUptiResult status;</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">  CUpti_Activity </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">*</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">record </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">=</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> NULL</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">;</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">  </span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\">  // This callback is running in a separate thread, so thread safety is essential</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">  </span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\">  // Process all records in the buffer</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">  do</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> {</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">    status </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">=</span><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\"> cuptiActivityGetNextRecord</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(buffer, validSize, </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">&#x26;</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">record);</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">    if</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> (status </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">==</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> CUPTI_SUCCESS) {</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\">      // Process the record - must be quick and non-blocking</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">      printActivity</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(record);</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">      </span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\">      // Move to the next record</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">      validSize </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">-=</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> record->common.size;</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">      buffer </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">+=</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> record->common.size;</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">    }</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">    else</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\"> if</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> (status </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">!=</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> CUPTI_ERROR_MAX_LIMIT_REACHED) {</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\">      // Handle any errors</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">      CUPTI_CALL</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(status);</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">    }</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">  } </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">while</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> (status </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">==</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> CUPTI_SUCCESS);</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">  </span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\">  // Free the buffer - must be the same pointer returned by bufferRequested</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">  free</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(buffer);</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">}</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<p><strong>Important notes about this callback:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>It runs in a separate thread from your application</li>\n<li>It should return quickly to avoid slowing down buffer processing</li>\n<li>Any data structures accessed in this callback must be thread-safe</li>\n<li>The buffer must be freed in this callback to avoid memory leaks</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"4-record-processing\">4. Record Processing</h3>\n<p>The record processing is similar to the synchronous version:</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"cpp\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"cpp\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">static</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\"> void</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">printActivity</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(CUpti_Activity </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">*</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">record)</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">{</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">  switch</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> (record->kind) {</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">  case</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> CUPTI_ACTIVITY_KIND_DEVICE:</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">    {</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\">      // Print device info</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">      CuptiActivityDevice </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">*</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">device </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">=</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> (CuptiActivityDevice </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">*</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">)record;</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">      printf</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">\"DEVICE </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">%s</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> (</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">%u</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">), capability </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">%u</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">.</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">%u</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">, ...</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">\\n</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">\"</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">,</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">             device->name, device->id,</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">             device->computeCapabilityMajor, device->computeCapabilityMinor);</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">      break</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">;</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">    }</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">  case</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> CUPTI_ACTIVITY_KIND_KERNEL:</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">    {</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\">      // Print kernel info</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">      CUpti_ActivityKernel4 </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">*</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">kernel </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">=</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> (CUpti_ActivityKernel4 </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">*</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">)record;</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">      printf</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">\"KERNEL </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">\\\"%s\\\"</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> [ </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">%llu</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> - </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">%llu</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> ] device </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">%u</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">, context </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">%u</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">, stream </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">%u\\n</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">\"</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">,</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">             kernel->name,</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">             (</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">unsigned</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\"> long</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\"> long</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">)(kernel->start </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">-</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> startTimestamp),</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">             (</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">unsigned</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\"> long</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\"> long</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">)(kernel->end </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">-</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> startTimestamp),</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">             kernel->deviceId, kernel->contextId, kernel->streamId);</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">      break</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">;</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">    }</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\">  // ... other activity types ...</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">  }</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">}</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<p><code>CuptiActivityDevice</code> is defined in <code>common/cupti_activity_compat.h</code>. It selects <code>CUpti_ActivityDevice6</code> for CUPTI 13.2 and newer, while CUDA 12.9 and other earlier supported toolkits continue to use <code>CUpti_ActivityDevice5</code>.</p>\n<h3 id=\"5-test-kernel-and-main-function\">5. Test Kernel and Main Function</h3>\n<p>The sample includes a simple vector addition kernel to generate profiling data:</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"cpp\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"cpp\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">__global__ </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">void</span><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\"> vecAdd</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">const</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\"> float</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\"> *</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">A, </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">const</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\"> float</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\"> *</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">B, </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">float</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\"> *</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">C, </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">int</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> numElements)</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">{</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">  int</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> i </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">=</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> blockDim.x </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">*</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> blockIdx.x </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">+</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> threadIdx.x;</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">  if</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> (i </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">&#x3C;</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> numElements)</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">    C[i] </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">=</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> A[i] </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">+</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> B[i];</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">}</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"> </span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">int</span><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\"> main</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">int</span><span style=\"color:#F69D50\"> argc</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">, </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">char</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\"> *</span><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">argv</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">[])</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">{</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\">  // Initialize CUPTI tracing</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">  initTrace</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">();</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">  </span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\">  // Allocate and initialize vectors</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\">  // ...</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">  </span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\">  // Launch the kernel</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">  dim3 </span><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">threadsPerBlock</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">256</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">);</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">  dim3 </span><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">blocksPerGrid</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">((N </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">+</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> threadsPerBlock.x </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">-</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> 1</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">) </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">/</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> threadsPerBlock.x);</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">  vecAdd</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">&#x3C;&#x3C;&#x3C;</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">blocksPerGrid, threadsPerBlock</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">>>></span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(d_A, d_B, d_C, N);</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">  </span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\">  // Copy results back to host</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">  cudaMemcpy</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(h_C, d_C, size, cudaMemcpyDeviceToHost);</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">  </span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\">  // Verify results</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\">  // ...</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">  </span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\">  // Finalize tracing - ensure all data is flushed</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">  finiTrace</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">();</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">  </span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">  return</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> 0</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">;</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">}</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<h3 id=\"6-finalizing-the-trace\">6. Finalizing the Trace</h3>\n<p>When your application is done, make sure to flush all remaining buffers:</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"cpp\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"cpp\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">void</span><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\"> finiTrace</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">()</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">{</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\">  // Flush any activity records still in buffers</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">  CUPTI_CALL</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(</span><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">cuptiActivityFlushAll</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">0</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">));</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">}</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<h2 id=\"running-the-sample\">Running the Sample</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>Build the sample:</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">make</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Run the asynchronous tracer:</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">./activity_trace_async</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"understanding-the-output\">Understanding the Output</h2>\n<p>The output shows all GPU activities with timestamps:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"\">DEVICE Device Name (0), capability 7.0, global memory (bandwidth 900 GB/s, size 16000 MB), multiprocessors 80, clock 1530 MHz\nCONTEXT 1, device 0, compute API CUDA, NULL stream 1\nDRIVER_API cuCtxCreate [ 10223 - 15637 ] \nMEMCPY HtoD [ 22500 - 23012 ] device 0, context 1, stream 7, correlation 1/1\nKERNEL \"vecAdd\" [ 32058 - 35224 ] device 0, context 1, stream 7, correlation 2\nMEMCPY DtoH [ 40388 - 41002 ] device 0, context 1, stream 7, correlation 3/3\n</code></pre>\n<p>The timestamps (in brackets) show when each operation started and ended, normalized to the beginning of the trace.</p>\n<h2 id=\"performance-considerations\">Performance Considerations</h2>\n<p>Asynchronous tracing offers several performance benefits:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Reduced Overhead</strong>: The main application thread continues running while activity records are processed in a separate thread</li>\n<li><strong>Lower Latency</strong>: CUDA operations aren't blocked waiting for buffer processing</li>\n<li><strong>Better Scalability</strong>: Works well for long-running applications or production monitoring</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"advanced-usage-tips\">Advanced Usage Tips</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Buffer Size Tuning</strong>: Adjust <code>BUF_SIZE</code> based on your application:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Larger buffers reduce callback frequency but use more memory</li>\n<li>Smaller buffers use less memory but may increase callback overhead</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Selective Tracing</strong>: Only enable the activity kinds you need:</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"cpp\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"cpp\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\">// If you only care about kernels, just enable these</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">cuptiActivityEnable</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(CUPTI_ACTIVITY_KIND_KERNEL);</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">cuptiActivityEnable</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(CUPTI_ACTIVITY_KIND_CONCURRENT_KERNEL);</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Thread Safety</strong>: When implementing your own version, ensure any data structures accessed by the buffer completion callback are thread-safe.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"next-steps\">Next Steps</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Try enabling different activity kinds to see different aspects of your application</li>\n<li>Modify the code to store records in a database or file for later analysis</li>\n<li>Implement a custom visualization tool to help understand the timeline data</li>\n<li>Try running the asynchronous tracer on your own CUDA applications</li>\n</ul>","tags":[],"headings":[{"id":"introduction","text":"Introduction","depth":2},{"id":"what-youll-learn","text":"What You'll Learn","depth":2},{"id":"asynchronous-vs-synchronous-tracing","text":"Asynchronous vs. Synchronous Tracing","depth":2},{"id":"code-walkthrough","text":"Code Walkthrough","depth":2},{"id":"1-setting-up-asynchronous-buffer-handling","text":"1. Setting Up Asynchronous Buffer Handling","depth":3},{"id":"2-asynchronous-buffer-request-callback","text":"2. Asynchronous Buffer Request Callback","depth":3},{"id":"3-asynchronous-buffer-completion-callback","text":"3. Asynchronous Buffer Completion Callback","depth":3},{"id":"4-record-processing","text":"4. Record Processing","depth":3},{"id":"5-test-kernel-and-main-function","text":"5. Test Kernel and Main Function","depth":3},{"id":"6-finalizing-the-trace","text":"6. Finalizing the Trace","depth":3},{"id":"running-the-sample","text":"Running the Sample","depth":2},{"id":"understanding-the-output","text":"Understanding the Output","depth":2},{"id":"performance-considerations","text":"Performance Considerations","depth":2},{"id":"advanced-usage-tips","text":"Advanced Usage Tips","depth":2},{"id":"next-steps","text":"Next Steps","depth":2}],"sourcePath":"https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/eunomia.dev/tree/main/docs/others/cupti-tutorial/activity_trace_async/README.md","metadata":{"updatedAt":"2026-07-22T08:40:15.000Z","createdAt":"2025-06-17T09:19:24.000Z","authors":[{"name":"github-actions[bot]","email":"41898282+github-actions[bot]@users.noreply.github.com"}]},"path":"/others/cupti-tutorial/activity_trace_async/","alternates":{"en":"/others/cupti-tutorial/activity_trace_async/","zh":"/zh/others/cupti-tutorial/activity_trace_async/"},"continuation":{"index":{"title":"About Eunomia","description":"The broader Eunomia project family, including GPU tutorials, research notes, experiments, and related open-source tools.","href":"/others/"},"previous":{"title":"basic-cuda-tutorial","description":"You can find the code in <https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/basic-cuda-tutorial","href":"/others/cuda-tutorial/"},"next":{"title":"CUPTI Activity Trace Tutorial","description":"The GitHub repo and complete tutorial is available at <https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/cupti-tutorial.","href":"/others/cupti-tutorial/activity_trace/"}},"sidebar":[{"title":"About Eunomia","items":[{"title":"About Eunomia","href":"/others/","depth":0},{"title":"BPF-Benchmark","href":"/others/bpf-benchmark/","depth":1},{"title":"bpf-compatible","href":"/others/bpf-compatible/","depth":1},{"title":"Contributing to eunomia-bpf","href":"/others/contribute/","depth":1},{"title":"Tutorial: Your First CUDA Program - Vector Addition","href":"/others/cuda-tutorial/01-vector-addition/","depth":2},{"title":"Tutorial: Understanding GPU Assembly with PTX","href":"/others/cuda-tutorial/02-ptx-assembly/","depth":2},{"title":"CUDA Programming Methods Comparison: Matrix Multiplication","href":"/others/cuda-tutorial/03-gpu-programming-methods/","depth":2},{"title":"Tutorial: Understanding GPU Architecture and Execution Model","href":"/others/cuda-tutorial/04-gpu-architecture/","depth":2},{"title":"Tutorial: Neural Network Forward Pass on GPU","href":"/others/cuda-tutorial/05-neural-network/","depth":2},{"title":"Tutorial: CNN Convolution with Shared Memory Optimization","href":"/others/cuda-tutorial/06-cnn-convolution/","depth":2},{"title":"Attention Mechanism for Transformer Models with CUDA","href":"/others/cuda-tutorial/07-attention-mechanism/","depth":2},{"title":"CUDA GPU Profiling and Tracing","href":"/others/cuda-tutorial/08-profiling-tracing/","depth":2},{"title":"GPU Application Extension Mechanisms: Modifying Behavior Without Source Code Changes","href":"/others/cuda-tutorial/09-gpu-extension/","depth":2},{"title":"CPU and GPU Profiling Boundaries: What to Measure Where","href":"/others/cuda-tutorial/10-cpu-gpu-profiling-boundaries/","depth":2},{"title":"Fine-Grained GPU Code Modifications","href":"/others/cuda-tutorial/11-fine-grained-gpu-modifications/","depth":2},{"title":"Advanced GPU Customizations","href":"/others/cuda-tutorial/12-advanced-gpu-customizations/","depth":2},{"title":"Low-Latency GPU Packet Processing","href":"/others/cuda-tutorial/13-low-latency-gpu-packet-processing/","depth":2},{"title":"CUDA Function Type Annotations: A Comprehensive Guide","href":"/others/cuda-tutorial/14-cuda-function-annotations/","depth":2},{"title":"OpenCL Basic Example - Vector Addition Explanation","href":"/others/cuda-tutorial/15-opencl-vector-addition/","depth":2},{"title":"PTX File Loading and Execution Demo","href":"/others/cuda-tutorial/README_PTX_Demo/","depth":2},{"title":"basic-cuda-tutorial","href":"/others/cuda-tutorial/","depth":1},{"title":"CUPTI Asynchronous Activity Tracing Tutorial","href":"/others/cupti-tutorial/activity_trace_async/","depth":2},{"title":"CUPTI Activity Trace Tutorial","href":"/others/cupti-tutorial/activity_trace/","depth":2},{"title":"CUPTI Autorange Profiling Tutorial","href":"/others/cupti-tutorial/autorange_profiling/","depth":2},{"title":"CUPTI Callback Event Tutorial","href":"/others/cupti-tutorial/callback_event/","depth":2},{"title":"CUPTI Performance Metrics Tutorial","href":"/others/cupti-tutorial/callback_metric/","depth":2},{"title":"CUPTI Callback-Based Profiling Tutorial","href":"/others/cupti-tutorial/callback_profiling/","depth":2},{"title":"CUPTI Timestamp Callback Tutorial","href":"/others/cupti-tutorial/callback_timestamp/","depth":2},{"title":"CUPTI Checkpoint API Tutorial","href":"/others/cupti-tutorial/checkpoint_kernels/","depth":2},{"title":"CUPTI Common Helper Files","href":"/others/cupti-tutorial/common/","depth":2},{"title":"CUPTI Concurrent Profiling Tutorial","href":"/others/cupti-tutorial/concurrent_profiling/","depth":2},{"title":"CUDA Graphs Tracing Tutorial","href":"/others/cupti-tutorial/cuda_graphs_trace/","depth":2},{"title":"CUDA Memory Tracing Tutorial","href":"/others/cupti-tutorial/cuda_memory_trace/","depth":2},{"title":"CUPTI API-GPU Activity Correlation Tutorial","href":"/others/cupti-tutorial/cupti_correlation/","depth":2},{"title":"CUPTI External Correlation Tutorial","href":"/others/cupti-tutorial/cupti_external_correlation/","depth":2},{"title":"CUPTI Finalization and Cleanup Tutorial","href":"/others/cupti-tutorial/cupti_finalize/","depth":2},{"title":"CUPTI Metric Properties Tutorial","href":"/others/cupti-tutorial/cupti_metric_properties/","depth":2},{"title":"CUPTI NVTX Integration Tutorial","href":"/others/cupti-tutorial/cupti_nvtx/","depth":2},{"title":"CUPTI Query API Tutorial","href":"/others/cupti-tutorial/cupti_query/","depth":2},{"title":"CUPTI Trace Injection Tutorial","href":"/others/cupti-tutorial/cupti_trace_injection/","depth":2},{"title":"CUP